            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot Gardens ¶ 17 Sept 1857 ¶ Reverend Sir ¶  ¶ My brother in law, Dr Edw. Wehl, informs me, that you were desirous of opening a botanical correspondence with me. In anticipation of this, I b...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">57.09.17</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Julian Tenison Woods</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Archives, Sisters of St Joseph, Perthville, NSW.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Photocopy — original letter not found.</p>
               </note>Melbourne bot Gardens</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17 Sept 1857</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Reverend Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My brother in law, Dr Edw. Wehl, informs me, that you were desirous of opening a botanical correspondence with me. In anticipation of this, I beg to adress you, and to express my sincere pleasure of having the opportunity of enjoying the intercourse with a gentleman of your high attainments.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In this busy part of the globe, we are all getting beyond much ceremony; I hope you will therefore pardon me for molesting you at once with a few questions.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would it be possible to get in flower and fruit a set of specimens from the botanically little known scrubs of Morris' station near Guichen Bay, to which I paid only a passing visit 9 years ago.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am particularly anxious for flower — and fruit — specimens of the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">red</hi>
               </seg> Honeysuckle (<name key="Banksia">Banksia</name>) a dwarf species of the scrub of the Coorong; also for a portion of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ripe</hi>
               </seg> fruits of the Guichen Bay Native Apple.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Doughty, my brother in law, tells me, that in the Salt lakes of Mackintosh Run (Mosquito-plains a weed exists abundantly, of which I should be glad to examine specimens.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enclose a leaf of a plant from Kangaroo Island. A similar very <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">rare</hi>
               </seg> species with larger leaves and white flower-bunches grows on or near Mount Benson. Of this a suite of specimens and ripe seeds would be very welcome.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With this mail I beg to send you a little pamphlet, to show you, in what way novelties are published, and hope that you will be able to contribute to the continuation.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Obediently</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Rev Mr Woods</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="4"/>&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="4"/>&amp;c</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">On Eucalypti &amp;c Dr Wehl would be able to give instructions as regards collecting</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Banksia">Banksia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
